	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">infiniteneslives wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">byemu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I try to replace prg and chr to another game on a mapper3 board!(this board use the 74ls161)</div><br />Do you mean 74LS32?</div><br />the original mapper3 board use 74ls161 bank chr(some other board use 74hc161)ÔºÅ<br />I's only replace the prg+chr ics.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">infiniteneslives wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">byemu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">now i try to play the new game on a real famicom,but it seams can't bank the chr!<br />but it can bank in kazzo,why?<br />is it the ls161 too slow?</div><br /><br />Whatever discrete chip it is, it's probably not too slow.  Are you saying that the game dumps properly on the Kazzo?  I did notice awhile back that the provided kazzo mmc3 dumping script doesn't actually address all CHR.  I think it just cycles through on one pattern table.  So you could have wrong circuitry for one pattern table and proper for the other.  If the kazzo only reads from the proper pattern table you could have a good dump, but bad play.<br /><br />I re-wrote the script try this one and see if it dumps properly: <a href="https://dl.dropbox.com/u/18341918/mmc3_full.ad" class="postlink">mmc3_full.ad</a></div><br />mmc3 can via write 0x8000 and write 0x8001 mapper all the 256k chr.<br />mapper3 can via write 0x8000(to 0xffff) mapper chrs.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


